### Biased MLE estimator for $\sigma^2$ 

Consider $X_1,\dots,X_n \sim \text N(0, \sigma^2)$. The MLE for $\sigma^2$ is $\hat\sigma^2 = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^n X_i^2$.

